DIFFRENCE BETWEEN THE DELETE , DROP , TRUNCATE
  (IMAGINE A SHELF CONTATING BOOKS, EACH BOOK REPRESENTS THE SPECIFIC ROW)
  1) DELETE IS FOR REMOVING SPECIFIC BOOK WITH CONSTRAINTS LIKE DELETING ALL RED COVERD BOOKS OR DELETING ALL BOOKS FROM TOP SHELF IN DELETION PROCESS IT CAN BE UNDO OR ROLL BACK
  2)TRUNCATE IS FOR DELETING ALL THE RECORDS OR BOOK FROM THE SHELF . MEANING ALL THE ROWS ARE DELETED LEAVING TABLE ALONE. ONLY THE TABLE STRUCTURE WILL BE THERE WITHOUT ANY BOOKS . TRUNCATE CANNOT BE ROLL BACK OR UNOD
  3)DROP IS USED FOR REMOVING ALL RECORDS AND SHELF . IT LEAVES ONLY EMPTY SPACE. IT CANNOT BE ROLL BACK OR UNDO
